I'm debugging a sporadic NullReferenceException in C#. It happens on this line sometimes when parsing a CSV and printing results:

Console.WriteLine(customer.Name.ToUpper());

customer is created from a CSV row using a small mapper I wrote. Most rows work, but some crash. What's the best way to diagnose and harden this?

